###Formula

We can make a confidence interval for the difference of two proportions like this:

$\begin{align}
(\text{sample difference}) &\pm (\text{critical value})\left(\overset{\text{standard error}}{\text{of difference}}\right) \\\\
(\hat{p}_1-\hat{p}_2)&\pm z^* \sqrt{\dfrac{\hat{p}_1\left(1-\hat{p}_1\right)}{n_1}+\dfrac{\hat{p}_2\left(1-\hat{p}_2\right)}{n_2}}
\end{align}$

